'''''Dawn of Night''''' is the second book in the [[The Erevis Cale Trilogy]] by [[Paul S. Kemp]] featuring [[Erevis Cale]] and [[Drasek Riven]]. 

{{Quote|''The shadows recede from a lost temple in a forgotten wilderness.''

''The sun rises on a new calling for a man as loyal as he is mysterious.''

''The day's beginning finds [[Erevis Cale]] holding in his steady hands more power than he dared hope for &mdash; and more responsibility than he ever imagined.'' 

''For now, he will have to put his trust in a god served by thieves and born of chaos.''
}}
